description: Data sets with no data values in the last 3 periods (based on data set period type).
sqlQuery: with ds_lastupdate as (select datasetid, avg(date_part('day',  pe.enddate::timestamp - pe.startdate::timestamp))::int as interval  from dataset ds  left join period pe using(periodtypeid) group by datasetid),  ds_period as (select datasetid, dataelementid, periodid from dataset ds  left join period pe using(periodtypeid)  left join datasetelement using(datasetid)  where date_part('day', now() -  pe.enddate::timestamp)::int <= 3*date_part('day',  pe.enddate::timestamp - pe.startdate::timestamp)::int) select 'dataset_nonewdata' as indicator,  count(*)::varchar as value,  (100*count(*)/(select count(*) from dataset))::varchar || '%' as percent,  'Data sets with no data values in  the last 3 periods (based on data set period type).' as description from dataset  where datasetid not in  (select distinct datasetid from ds_period  where (dataelementid,periodid) in (select dataelementid,  periodid from datavalue) group by datasetid);
